data['Size'] = data['Size'].str.replace('M', '1000000').str.replace('K', '1000')

# Convert Size column to numeric data type
try:
    data['Size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Size'])
except:
    pass

# Drop entries where size='Varies with device'
data = data.drop(data[data['Size'] == 'Varies with device'].index)

# Check if Size column contains only numeric values
if pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(data['Size']):
    print('Size column successfully converted to numeric data type')
else:
    print('Size column still contains non-numeric values')

Size column still contains non-numeric values
In [36]:
mapping_dict = {'M': 1000000, 'K': 1000}

# Replace non-numeric values with corresponding numeric values
for index, row in data.iterrows():
    size_value = row['Size']
    for key, value in mapping_dict.items():
        if key in size_value:
            size_value = size_value.replace(key, str(value))
            row['Size'] = size_value

# Handle invalid values
invalid_values = data['Size'].str.contains('Varies with device').any()
if invalid_values:
    data.drop(data[data['Size'].str.contains('Varies with device')].index, inplace=True)

# Convert the size column to numeric data type
data['Size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Size'], errors='coerce')
